        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ard" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d3017e66" type="lemma"><orth>ard</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d3017e69"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>клятва</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>vow</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re xml:id="re_d3017e79">
                    <form xml:id="form_d3017e81" type="lemma"><orth>ard xæryn</orth></form>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d3017e84"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>клясться</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>swear</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp xml:id="exampleGrp_d3017e95">
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3017e97">
                        <quote>Nart sæ Acamongæjæ xordtoj ard</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Нарты клялись своей (чашей) Ацамонга</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>The Narts swore by their (bowl) Atzamonga</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            11</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3017e116">
                        <quote>calynmæ myn… syǵytæj ard baxæraj, walynmæ dyl næ
                            bawwændʒynæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пока ты мне не поклянешься землей, я тебе не поверю</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>until you swear by the ground, I won't believe you</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I
                            148</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3017e135">
                        <quote>ūj ta rajdydta ard xæryn æmæ somy kænyn: næ zonyn acy læǵy</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>он же начал клясться и божиться: не знаю человека сего</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>but he began to curse and to swear, saying, I know not this man</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Марк"/><biblScope><hi rendition="#rend_italic">14</hi>
                            71</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3017e154">
                        <quote>Teǵia fydæǧdaw racyd ænæwwænk, ænæard</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Теджиа стал безнравственным, лишенным доверия, лишенным <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">ard</hi>ʼa</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Tejia became immoral, deprived of trust, deprived of <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">ard</hi></q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>29</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3017e173">
                        <quote>ūsīmæ ard ḱī xæry, ūj ūsy x˳yzæn ū</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кто связывает себя клятвой с женщиной, тот (сам) подобен женщине</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>whoever binds himself with a vow to a woman, he (himself) is like a
                                woman</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>83—84</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3017e193">
                        <quote>ard dyn xæryn acy zæxxæj, somy dyn kænyn bærzond cʼæx arvæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>клянусь тебе этой землей, клянусь тебе высоким синим небом</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I swear to you by this land, I swear to you by the high blue sky</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>46</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3017e212">
                        <quote>ma ard myn ma fæsajyn kæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>не заставь меня нарушить клятву</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>don't make me break my vow</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>83</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3017e231">
                        <quote>ard dæ fædyl æftyd fæwæd!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>да преследует тебя <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">ard</hi>!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>may <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">ard</hi> haunt you!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            119</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3017e250" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>kizgaj, dæ art <hi rendition="#rend_italic">(sic!)</hi> cæmæn sajis?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>девушка, почему ты нарушаешь свою клятву</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>girl why are you breaking your vow</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            87</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e534" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e275" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*ṛta</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e539" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e280" xml:lang="ira"><w>arta-</w></mentioned>.
                    Значение ‘клятва’ не покрывает семантику этого слова, на что указывает и наличие
                    в осетинском других слов для ‘клятвы’: и. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_somy"/>,
                    д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wasxæ"/>; в таких выражениях, как <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e546" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e287" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>x˳ycæwy ard</w>
                        <gloss><q>божий <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">ard</hi></q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e555" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e296" xml:lang="os"><w>adæmy ard</w>
                        <gloss><q><hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">ard</hi> народа</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e561" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e302" xml:lang="os"><w>ard dæ bajjafæd</w>
                        <gloss><q><hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">ard</hi> тебя да настигнет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e567" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e308" xml:lang="os"><w>ard dæ fædyl æftyd fæwæd</w>
                        <gloss><q><hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">ard</hi> тебя да преследует</q></gloss></mentioned> , <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ard</hi>
                    понимается как „магическая“ сила. Культовое происхождение слова подтверждается
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e573" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e314" xml:lang="xln"><lang/>
                        <w>αρδ</w>
                        <gloss><q>бог</q></gloss></mentioned> в названии Феодосии Ἀρδαβδα ‘(город)
                    семи богов’; значение ‘клятва’ явилось, надо думать, результатом постоянного
                    употребления этого слова в формулах клятвы; ср. аналогичное семантическое
                    развитие адыгского <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e581" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e322" xml:lang="ady"><lang/>
                        <w>wašx̣wä</w></mentioned>, которое в убыхском является названием божества,
                    в кабардинском употребительно только в формулах клятвы, а в осетинском получило
                    значение ‘клятва’ (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wasxæ"/>). Ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e589" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e330" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*art-</w></mentioned> в религиозных и календарных терминах [<mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e594" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e335" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>ʽrtw</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (← <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e600" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e341" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                                <w>*artavan-</w></mentioned>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e606" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e347" xml:lang="sog"><w>ʽrtʽwxwšt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e609" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e350" xml:lang="sog"><w>ʽrtɣwšt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e612" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e353" xml:lang="sog"><w>ʽrtxwšt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e615" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e356" xml:lang="sog"><w>ʽrtʽwʽspy</w></mentioned>], <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e619" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e360" xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
                        <w>arta-</w>
                        <gloss><q>божество Арта</q></gloss></mentioned>, а также в составе
                    собственного имени: <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Artaxšaθra-(Артаксеркс)</hi>, <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Артаферн</hi>, <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Артабан</hi>,
                    <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Артаксата</hi>, <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Артавазд</hi>, <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Артапат</hi> и др.; <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e627" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e368" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>aša-</w></mentioned> (из *<hi rendition="#rend_italic">arta</hi>-) — один из важнейших культовых
                    терминов Авесты, олицетворение ‘небесного света’, ‘благодати’, ‘правды’ и пр.:
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e632" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e373" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>ṛtá-</w>
                        <gloss><q>священный</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр.; сюда же относят
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e640" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e381" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>ard</w></mentioned> в <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e645" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e386" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>ard-ar</w>
                        <gloss><q>правдивый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e653" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e394" xml:lang="xcl"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>справедливый</q></gloss></mentioned> (ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e660" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e401" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>m-art-ali</w></mentioned> id.), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e665" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e406" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>erdumn</w>
                        <gloss><q>клятва</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e673" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e414" xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">рота</w>
                        <gloss><q>клятва</q></gloss></mentioned>; <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ṛtæ</hi>, <hi rendition="#rend_italic">arta</hi>- представляет,
                    по <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">НеrtеI</hi>'ю, один из дериватов корня ar- ‘небо-свет-огонь’ (<bibl><author>J.
                            Неrtеl</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Beitr. z. Erklärung d. Awestas
                            u. d. Vedas. 1929, стр. 20 сл.</biblScope></bibl>). Отмеченное в <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e686" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e428" xml:lang="syd-x-south"><lang>южносамоедских наречиях</lang>
                        <w>ārda</w>
                        <gloss><q>верно</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>правда</q></gloss>
                        <note type="bibl" xml:lang="ru">
                                    (<bibl><author>Donner</author><biblScope>Kamassisehes
                                    Worterbuch, 1944</biblScope></bibl>;
                                    <bibl><author>Joki</author><biblScope>Die Lehnwörter des
                                    Sajansamojedischen, 1952, s.v.</biblScope></bibl>Joki. Die
                            Lehnwδrter des Sajansamojedischen, 1952, s.v.)</note></mentioned>
                    представляет, возможно, старое заимствование из иранского. Глагол ‘присягать’,
                    ‘клясться’ выражается в осетинском через <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e706" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e450" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>ard xæryn</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">буквально</note>
                        <gloss><q>есть клятву</q></gloss></mentioned>, что связано с реальными
                    действиями при обряде присяги (поедается предмет, которым клянутся, см.
                            <bibl><biblScope>СМОМПК VII, отд. 1</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I 148</biblScope></bibl>:
                    герой Батрадз клянется землей и тут же бросает в рот горсть земли); ср.
                    аналогичные выражения в других иранских языках: <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e725" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e468" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>sougand xūrdan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e730" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e473" xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>sōgind warag</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e735" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e478" xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>sont xarən</w>
                        <gloss><q>клясться</q></gloss></mentioned>; тот же способ выражения — в
                    согдийском (<bibl><author>Salemann</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ИАН"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1907, стр. 544</biblScope></bibl>); ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e750" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e493" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>ærdxord</w>
                        <gloss><q>побратим</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e758" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e501" xml:lang="os"><w>ærdxæræn</w>
                        <gloss><q>прославленный</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">23
                            сл.</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><author>Bailey. Е. В.</author><biblScope>Ceadel. Literatures of
                            the East, 101</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">38, 71, 155, 195 сл.,
                            231</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e275" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e534" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*ṛta</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e280" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e539" xml:lang="ira"><w>arta-</w></mentioned>.
                    The meaning ‘vow’ does not cover the semantics of this word, which is also
                    indicated by the presence of other words for ‘vow’ in Ossetic: Iron <ref type="xr" target="#entry_somy"/>, Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wasxæ"/>; in such expressions as <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e287" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e546" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>x˳ycæwy ard</w>
                        <gloss><q>God's <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">ard</hi></q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e296" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e555" xml:lang="os"><w>adæmy ard</w>
                        <gloss><q>people's <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">ard</hi></q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e302" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e561" xml:lang="os"><w>ard dæ bajjafæd</w>
                        <gloss><q>may <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">ard</hi> reach you</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e308" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e567" xml:lang="os"><w>ard dæ fædyl æftyd fæwæd</w>
                        <gloss><q>may <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">ard</hi> haunt you</q></gloss></mentioned> , <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ard</hi> is
                    understood as “magic power”. A cult origin of the word is confirmed by
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e314" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e573" xml:lang="xln"><lang/>
                        <w>αρδ</w>
                        <gloss><q>бог</q></gloss></mentioned> in the name of Feodosia Ἀρδαβδα
                    ‘(town) of seven gods’; the meaning ‘vow’ was, presumably, the result of the
                    constant use of this word in the formulas of a vow; cf. similar semantic
                    development of the Adyghe <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e322" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e581" xml:lang="ady"><lang/>
                        <w>wašx̣wä</w></mentioned>, which in Ubykh is the name of a deity, in
                    Kabardian it is used only in vow formulas, and in Ossetic it has received the
                    meaning ‘vow’ (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wasxæ"/>). Cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e330" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e589" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*art-</w></mentioned> in religious and calendar terms [<mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e335" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e594" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>ʽrtw</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (← <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e341" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e600" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                                <w>*artavan-</w></mentioned>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e347" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e606" xml:lang="sog"><w>ʽrtʽwxwšt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e350" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e609" xml:lang="sog"><w>ʽrtɣwšt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e353" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e612" xml:lang="sog"><w>ʽrtxwšt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e356" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e615" xml:lang="sog"><w>ʽrtʽwʽspy</w></mentioned>], <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e360" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e619" xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
                        <w>arta-</w>
                        <gloss><q>deity Arta</q></gloss></mentioned>, and also as a part of the
                    proper name: <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Artaxšaθra-(Артаксеркс)</hi>, <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Артаферн</hi>, <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Артабан</hi>,
                    <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Артаксата</hi>, <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Артавазд</hi>, <hi rendition="#rend_italic">Артапат</hi> etc.; <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e368" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e627" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>aša-</w></mentioned> (from *<hi rendition="#rend_italic">arta</hi>-) — one of the most important cult
                    terms of Avesta, the personification of ‘heavenly light’, ‘grace’, ‘truth’,
                    etc.: <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e373" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e632" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>ṛtá-</w>
                        <gloss><q>holy</q></gloss></mentioned> etc.; also here <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e381" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e640" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>ard</w></mentioned> belongs in <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e386" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e645" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>ard-ar</w>
                        <gloss><q>faithful</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e394" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e653" xml:lang="xcl"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fair</q></gloss></mentioned> (cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e401" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e660" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>m-art-ali</w></mentioned> id.), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e406" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e665" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>erdumn</w>
                        <gloss><q>vow</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e414" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e673" xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>rota</w>
                        <gloss><q>vow</q></gloss></mentioned>; according to <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">Неrtеl</hi>, <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ṛtæ</hi>,
                    <hi rendition="#rend_italic">arta</hi>- represents one of the derivatives of the root <hi rendition="#rend_italic">ar</hi>- ‘sky-light-fire’
                            (<bibl><author>J. Неrtеl</author><biblScope xml:lang="en">Beitr. z. Erklärung d. Awestas
                            u. d. Vedas. 1929, p. 20 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). The word <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e428" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e686" xml:lang="syd-x-south"><w>ārda</w>
                        <gloss><q>right</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>truth</q></gloss>
                        <note type="bibl" xml:lang="en">
                                    (<bibl><author>Donner</author><biblScope>Kamassisehes
                                    Worterbuch, 1944</biblScope></bibl>;
                                    <bibl><author>Joki</author><biblScope>Die Lehnwörter des
                                    Sajansamojedischen, 1952, s.v.</biblScope></bibl>Joki. Die
                            Lehnwδrter des Sajansamojedischen, 1952, s.v.)</note></mentioned>
                    attested in <hi rendition="#rend_bold">South Samoyedic</hi> dialects perhaps represents an old borrowing
                    from Iranian. The verb ‘to swear’, ‘make an oath’ is expressed in Ossetic by
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e450" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e706" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>ard xæryn</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">literally</note>
                        <gloss><q>eat vow</q></gloss></mentioned>, which is associated with real
                    actions during the ritual of the oath (the object that is sworn is eaten, see
                            <bibl><biblScope xml:lang="en">SMOMPK (Collection of materials for the description of
                            areas and tribes of the Caucasus) VII, section 1</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I
                            148</biblScope></bibl>: the hero Batradz swears by ground and
                    immediately throws a handful of the ground into his mouth); cf. similar
                    expressions in other Iranian languages: <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e468" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e725" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>sougand xūrdan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e473" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e730" xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>sōgind warag</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e478" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e735" xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>sont xarən</w>
                        <gloss><q>swear</q></gloss></mentioned>; the same way to express it is found
                    in Sogdian (<bibl><author>Salemann</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ИАН"/><biblScope xml:lang="en">1907, p. 544</biblScope></bibl>); cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e493" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e750" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>ærdxord</w>
                        <gloss><q>sworn brother</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3017e501" xml:id="mentioned_d3017e758" xml:lang="os"><w>ærdxæræn</w>
                        <gloss><q>famous</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope xml:lang="en">23 ff.</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><author>Bailey. Е. В.</author><biblScope>Ceadel. Literatures of
                            the East, 101</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope xml:lang="en">38, 71, 155, 195 ff.,
